		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3583"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3583')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=8658&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=PoM+Advanced%28puppets+aiw4+solo%29"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> so ive been bound in pom for months now, killed almost every mob in the zone at least once, in mirriads of groups</P><P>ive finally finished my red flower(have black, green, white, and now red flowers), and had the crowns i need for my robe(as well as my doll), so basically, i ONLY need thrones, 0 need for crowns and below(same for wow pieces)</P><P>so, this basically left me with 1 mob i could solo for thrones, forrest chest, and thats boring as shit</P><P>now, ive been telling myself i wanted to solo a puppet, just as a challenge , just been waiting to catch them up</P><P>if you do pom often, youll notice the puppets some times 'bug' up<BR>as in, dont spawn/despawn wtih BB/geb</P><P>well, ive learned how to 'bug' them up, and its a simple task, just as easy as killing Geb to stop from BB from spawning(and prolly as legit, script wise)</P><P>now to do this, you must 1st learn how to solo puppets(3 tribunalts if your not kos to inny, less if you are), tunare puppets, and grink/glonk4, because, to 'bug' them up, you gotta kill Geb once, tribunals/tunare , (geb > glonk4 difficulty wise)<BR>actually, now that i think about it, think only non kos classes to inny can do this<BR>reasn for thsi being, when fighting middle tribunal, when you get summoned, your within innys melee range, and youll get hit(inny hits for 345s)</P><P>now how to keep the puppets up you need to :<BR>kill Geb per normal requirements(before 9am etc..)<BR>kill the 3 tribunals, and the tunare puppet<BR>oddly enough, these are the only ones i could solo(culd clear all but rallos if it wasnt for the way summon range works)</P><P>after this is down, the next eq day, BB spawns at 7am, despawns everything thats left up(audience/puppets), but puppets/audience members spawn as usual from 8-9am, with nothing popping to despawn them(wtihout you having to fuck with geb)</P><P>killing nothing but 3tribs and tunare, you can keep this cycle going for as long as you want(havent exactly figured out whihc puppet(s) is the trigger, or if order matters), i know 1 trib + tunare = BB popping at 8am, which sort of works, when BB pops at 8am, he despawns the 'fresh' tunare/bbpuppet, which may not allow the 'bug' to continue the next eq day(gonna find out soon enough, this is happening as i type)</P><P>well, thats how to technically how to bug them up, now to be able to klil these mobs you gotta root/dot a summoning mob(puppets are slightly diff, ill get to them after(much easier))</P><P>lets take grink4 for an example<BR>lvl54-55rat, 20k hp, hits for about 161-165, moderate atk</P><P>im 60, wtih mastery3, FT9, pyre, epic(doesnt matter here), Zheart, 10th ring, elder beads,  2620hp unbuffed etc..so your milage may vary here</P><P>the concept is simple, hit num lock when the summon is coming, oyu take a minimal amount of melee dmg(usually 1round of melee or less)<BR>between summons you have 9sec to med, cast, swap spells etc..<BR>eventually you get a good sense of summon timing</P><P>pom is a serious place to experiment with this, since hte mobs put out substantial dps, and have huge hp to back it up, so its really a study in effeciency/dps on your part<BR>personally, i buff up with 10th ring, dmf, sotm, spirit armor(yes spirit armor), and banshee aura, the DS REALLY helps out in these long fights(22point DS there, ill parse a fight one of these days, my guess is it does over 1-2k dmg per ifght just off DS)</P><P>spells memmed : flux, vexing, pye, splurt, PE, QVoX, dooming, FD</P><P>mid fight i bounce in pyre/ignite blood in the splurt slot when appropirate, </P><P>the extra dps from the swapped spells is pretty needed, since you hvae x amount of time to kill these mobs(more evident on glonk4), that x amount being your hp/rune total</P><P>you have about 3-4% of hp before htey start summoning to swap spells in/out, so i usually do PE/dooming/splurt/ignite/pyro, then start pyre/vex up after summons start</P><P>PE usually holds for full, or close to that in pom, so you dont have to bounce around alot with roots</P><P>for getting the hang of this, i reccomend starting with grink2 and working your way up grink/glonks up to 4</P><P>glonk4 is slightly diff, hes a big ass monkey(lvl57btw), and your a big ass spec, so that means, each summon = 2 melee rounds<BR>for glonk4, i use demi lich instead of AL and it seems to aleviate this some(its still usually 1.5melee rounds), but hes got alot of hp, and has big dps, so you need to REALLY get the balance right on glonk<BR>even after doing htsi for a few weeks now, glonk fights can come down to a QVoX past enrange hoping he flees for me(depending on melee rolls obviously)</P><P>for reference, doing this technique, glonk > grink > glenn/brenn(these need splitting of course)</P><P>once you get the handle of htis, your rdy for Geb, geb is kinda like glonk4, but tiny, and more dps outta him(196max vs 165 on glonk4)</P><P>and you only have from 6am-9am to kill him, so you cant really dilly dally around</P><P>once oyuve killed geb, you get to reap the rewards of your hard work</P><P>hte puppets</P><P>tribunals hit for 165s, tunare hits for 195s, </P><P>puppets have 32k</P><P>whta makes these fights MUCh easier is that..., theyre really not rooted<BR>as in, they dont have root/undead aggro, meaning<BR>you can break out your spec pet, and go to town</P><P>i set up facing the corner, dots i use are normally: splurt, pyre, pyro, vex, ebolt/devouring dark(taunt factor), load up heavy dots at the start, send pet after 1st summon, enjoy 45dps from your pet fr the duration of the fight(spec parses at 45dps againts puppets wtih the 65% pet buff, not counting procs), fights are about the same duration of alice4 fights, even tho the hp is much higher here(20k vs 32k)<BR>same thing , hit num lock when you feel a summon coming, med/cast between summons, and your golden, vex/flux when needed(the feel for this develops as you do it more often), puppets dont drain the mana pool as bad as alice4<BR>only precautions, if your kos to inny puppet, you cant really do this, when being summoned by a mid/right tribunal, your within innny melee range, which = pain(if your taking 2 pupptes worth of dmg)<BR>same thing with inny and rallos, i could do inny if it wasnt for rallos, same wtih everything around ralos baiscally, solusek and erollisa are wusses(165 and 245)</P><P>well there you go</P><P>doing/knowing that, you could solo yourself all 5 fowers, and solo/quest the best necro robe pre emp/vt</P><P>in a 68min block, i can clear puppets, and alice4 and have some time to relax between kills, each mob gives 3% xp, thats 8mobs, which = 24% xp an hour, so the xp isnt bad doing this either</P><P></P><P>Lich Kriista Silence<BR>Warlock of Veeshan</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458</a></font></td>

